<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senate, Chamber of Deputies Presidents Elected </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1203140494 Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional in Spanish 0000 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1203140494 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] [passage omitted] Gabriel Valdes was elected 
today as Senate president, and Socialist Senator Ricardo Nunez 
as Senate vice president, thus concluding one of the most 
anecdotal chapters of Chilean policy. According to a political 
agreement reached at the last minute, National Renewal Party, 
RN, Senator Sergio Diez will assume the position as Senate 
president in 1996, and Independent Democratic Union leader 
Eugenio Cantuarias will become the Senate vice president. One 
year later, RN Senator Sergio Romero will become the Senate 
president, while Cantuarias will continue in his position as 
Senate vice president. [passage omitted] 
  Party for Democracy Deputy Jorge Schaulsohn was elected 
Chamber of Deputies chairman with 65 votes against 51 votes 
received by rightist Independent Democratic Union candidate 
Andres Chadwick. Christian Democratic Party leader Juan Carlos 
Latorre was elected first vice chairman with 68 votes against 51 
votes obtained by RN leader Marina Prochelle. RN Deputy Alberto 
Espina was elected second vice chairman with 95 votes. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

