<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Communique Defines Media Restrictions for Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1303154494 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0130 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1303154494 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique issued by Communications Minister William </F>
Jaramillo in Santa Fe de Bogota; date not given; from the "TV 
Today" newscast] 
  [Text] The communications minister reminds all radio 
broadcasting media, television stations, cable television 
companies, and regional television organizations to comply with 
the following electoral rules: 
  1. The broadcast of video or voice campaign 
advertisements is prohibited as of 0000 on 12 March until the 
polls are closed on 13 March 1994. 
  2. There is a ban on radio and television interviews with 
the candidates during the same period. 
  3. Only public order reports confirmed by official 
sources may be broadcast on election day. 
  4. In accordance with Decree No. 397 of 1994, Article 3, 
the media may disseminate information on the electoral results 
only after the polls close. 
  5. During the voting, the media may only report on the 
number of people who cast their votes and indicate the 
corresponding voting tables. 
  6. In accordance with National Electoral Council 
Resolution No. 066 of 1994, Article 1, no results or predictions 
based on data obtained from exit polls may be broadcast. 
  7. In accordance with National Electoral Council 
Resolution No. 066 of 1994, Paragraph 1, no predictions or 
projections may be broadcast, even if they are based on polls or 
official data. 
  8. The Communications Ministry will ensure compliance 
with Law 84 of 1993, Decree Nos. 397, 463, and 540 of 1994, 
National Electoral Council Resolution Nos. 075 of 1993 and 066 
of 1994, and current legal provisions to guarantee the integrity 
of the electoral process. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

