  [Text] Here is the first bulletin of the Liberal Party's 
[PL] internal primary. These results represent 2 percent of the 
tables; out of 45,837 tables, 946 have been counted. The 
potential number of male voters are 8,603,751, for female 
voters, 8,429,199. 
  The first bulletin of the Liberal Party's internal primary 
shows the following results: 
  Ernesto Samper Pizano is in first place, with 21,477 votes, 
representing 39.7 percent; second is Rodolfo Gonzalez with 
12,286 votes, or 22.7 percent; third, Humberto de la Calle 
Lombana, with 6,556 votes, or 12.1 percent; fourth, Carlos 
Lleras de la Fuente, with 3,262 votes, or 6 percent. 
  The other candidates follow in this order: David 
Turbay--1,872 votes, or 3.4 percent; Carlos Lemos 
Simmonds--1,715, or 3.1 percent; Gloria Gaitan--1,204 votes, or 
2.2 percent. 
  Total number of blank votes--2,739; null votes--2,958; total 
number of votes counted--54,059. 

