<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   ELN Kidnaps Electoral Officials in Carcasi, Santander </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1303191594 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1800 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1303191594 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "NTC News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The guerrillas have tried in vain to thwart the 
democratic determination of hundreds of Colombians in an 
extensive area of Santander Department. The Efrain Pabon Front 
of the ELN [Army of National Liberation] kidnapped 31 [number as 
heard] delegates and voting officers in Carcasi, (Garcia 
Rovira). Meanwhile, efficient operations by the authorities have 
allowed voting to take place normally in the area. 
  [Begin recording] [Reporter] The delegates and officers were 
traveling in five vehicles when they were intercepted by an ELN 
front in Carcasi Municipality, eastern Santander Department. 
The subversives are holding seven National Civil Registry 
Office delegates and 25 students who were going to (Toboson) to 
serve as voting officers. The guerrillas freed the driver of 
one vehicle, who subsequently informed the authorities. 
  [Second Division Commander Manuel Bonnet; identified by 
caption] We have been helping the National Civil Registry 
Office and the Governor's Office since this morning. We have 
the material here at the brigade and are ready to transport it 
via helicopter. The troops are also ready to ensure that the 
elections are held in those areas. 
  [Reporter] The kidnapping occurred on the afternoon of 12 
March, and by that evening the National Civil Registry Office 
had dispatched new delegates to see that elections would be held 
in the place where the subversive incursion occurred. The 
military forces said the elections are progressing normally in 
that zone. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

