<H3> <TI>   Peasant Crisis Prompts Replacements of Officials </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1103202994 Asuncion NOTICIAS in Spanish 9 Mar 94 p 23 </F>
<F P=103> PY1103202994 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion NOTICIAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] On 8 March Paraguayan President Juan Carlos 
Wasmosy appointed Mario Lujan Melgarejo as acting president of 
the National Development Bank [BNF] replacing Rolando Eligio 
Bogado Martinez who was thanked for his services as head of the 
BNF. 
  The appointment of Mario Lujan Melgarejo, a economist by 
profession, is the second time President Wasmosy has replaced a 
key official in his administration since the peasant crisis 
began. The peasants criticized the Agrarian Reform Institute, 
the BNF, and the Agricultural Development Fund for not serving 
the interests of farmers. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

