<H3> <TI>   LAPSA Announces Suspension of All Flights </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1203002094 Asuncion ABC COLOR in Spanish 9 Mar 94 p 17 </F>
<F P=103> PY1203002094 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ABC COLOR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] "Ladies and gentlemen, Paraguayan Airlines 
[LAPSA] announces the suspension of all its flights." This is 
the announcement that might have been expected, but it was never 
uttered. The lack of money said everything, and therefore the 
airplanes did not fly yesterday, operations being suspended 
until the company is privatized. If the airline had continued 
to operate it would have lost $4.3 million this month. A quick 
decision by Congress is expected for its privatization. The 
bill will be submitted to the Chamber of Deputies on 10 March. 
  Yesterday at noon, the LAPSA Board of Directors suspended 
the 
DC-10 flight to Miami. Then the Privatization Council announced 
to the Board of Directors the suspension of all flights. The 
operations were suspended because without state aid the company 
had no funds to continue operating. The president of the 
Bicameral Privatization Committee said if operations continued 
the company would lose $4.3 million in March alone. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

