<H3> <TI>   Cardenist Candidate Criticizes Camacho </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1203143094 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0430 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1203143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Rafael Aguilar Talamantes, presidential candidate 
for the Cardenist Front for National Reconstruction [PFCRN], 
visited Leon, Guanajuato, and commented on statements made by 
Manuel Camacho Solis. 
  [Begin Aguilar recording] Today more than ever, and after 
hearing Camacho's Messianic words, I am more convinced that the 
PFCRN and its supporters must work hard to ensure a victory in 
the 21 August elections. With those illuminating statements he 
is asking the homeland to pay for services rendered and 
recognize him as a savior. He said this country will be 
