<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ruiz Says Chiapas Peace Talks To Resume in 2 Weeks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1203015394 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1203015394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to Bishop Samuel Ruiz Garcia, the second 
stage of the talks for peace and reconciliation in Chiapas will 
start in about two weeks. The purpose of this second stage is to 
sign the peace agreements. 
  Ruiz has been in the headlines because of the death threats 
he has received and the demands of certain San Cristobal de las 
Casas conservative groups' that Ruiz leave the San Cristobal de 
las Casas diocese. Ruiz said the meetings with the EZLN rank and 
file are in depth and serious. If this is so, the delegates 
would return in two weeks and the beginning of the talks would 
be announced 24 hours beforehand. 

</TEXT>

