<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Views Cooperation Prospects </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1403162694 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1500 GMT 
14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1403162694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina has said that 
our country wants to increase cooperation and trade with other 
countries in order to be adequately reincorporated into the new 
international economic context, with the advantage that, 
notwithstanding its setbacks, Cuba also has things to offer. 
  In his tour of Asian countries, Robaina said that economic 
and trade prospects with Indonesia are very promising and that 
the two countries are also interested in strengthening the 
Nonaligned Movement. 
  Robaina added: During our visit to Bangkok we met with Thai 
Foreign Minister Prasong Sunsiri. The meeting allowed us to 
study formulas to increase our economic ties. Our next visits to 
Asia will seek the same objective. 
  Cuba is open to all forms of cooperation and, despite the 
U.S. pressure through the blockade, is day by day demonstrating 
its capacity to resist and its determination to succeed, Robaina 
concluded. 

</TEXT>

