<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Raul Castro Greets Ciego de Avila EJT Brigade </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1503020894 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 0100 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1503020894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] In Ciego de Avila, the first Youth Labor Army 
[EJT] brigade to cut 1 million arrobas of sugarcane in Cuba has 
received a letter of congratulations from Army General Raul 
Castro. 
  The average age of the brigade members is barely 18 years. 
However, they have been capable of the labor feat of cutting 1 
million arrobas in slightly less than 60 workdays. This result 
places them at the head of the EJT forces participating in the 
sugarcane harvest and is a repeat of last year's success. 
[passage omitted] 
  They have once again raised high their battalion flag -- the 
531st -- of the Batalla del Ubero Camp in Venezuela 
Municipality. The brigade members were happy to receive the 
letter of congratulations from Army Gen. Raul Castro for being 
an outstanding unit. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

