<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Views Ties With Bolivia, Cuba </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1403151494 Santiago Radio Cooperativa Network in Spanish 
1000 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1403151494 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago Radio Cooperativa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Telephone interview by Foreign Minister Carlos Figueroa </F>
Serrano by unidentified reporter; date and place not given -- 
live or recorded] 
  [Excerpt] [Passage omitted] [Reporter] Referring to some 
specific countries, it seems the path toward the resumption of 
diplomatic relations with Bolivia is being opened. Some people 
believe Cuba's isolation has hurt the Cuban people. What 
chances are there of resuming diplomatic relations with Bolivia 
and of establishing relations, at an ambassadorial level, with 
Cuba? 
  [Figueroa] I believe the first consideration in diplomatic 
relations are Chilean interests. Chile maintains relations with 
those countries that can help us to attain the 
political-economic objectives we seek. This must be considered 
when thinking about resuming relations. In the case of Bolivia, 
they broke relations with Chile, therefore, it is up to them to 
resume relations. In the case of Bolivia there is a climate of 
confidence, friendship, and even an economic cooperation 
agreement with that country. There are physical integration 
projects involving highways, port facilities, etc., that reveal 
the existence of a very good relationship between Chile and 
Bolivia at this moment. Let us hope it will lead to the 
establishment of diplomatic relations. 
  We maintain relations at a consular level with Cuba. We 
maintain commercial relations. Chilean businessmen are 
investing in Cuba and this must be considered when deciding to 
step up relations to an ambassadorial level, because a 
relationship does exist, as I have pointed out, at a consular 
level. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-10905 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat050_n_94005" </HT>


