<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Interior Ministry Communique on Demonstration </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1403192494 Asuncion ULTIMA HORA in Spanish 14 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PY1403192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ULTIMA HORA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Interior Ministry this morning issued a 
communique, addressed to the public, on the events scheduled for 
15 March. 
  The communique notes that in view of the various 
demonstrations by various sectors of society, the authorities 
responsible for domestic security and public order report -- in 
keeping with the people's constitutional rights and guarantees 
-- that they will guarantee the people's right to peacefully 
meet and demonstrate. 
  The communique also points out that the deployment of police 
patrols during these demonstrations will serve to protect the 
demonstrators and others who have nothing to do with the 
demonstration and will prevent acts of vandalism against public 
and private interests. 
  The communique ends by reminding those participating in the 
demonstrations that they must act within the limits established 
by their rights and prerogatives, without violating the rights 
of third parties and that the sponsors of these demonstrations 
are responsible for the development and outcome of the 
demonstration and the collective attitude of those participating. 

</TEXT>

