<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Justice Commission Chides PRD for Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1403164594 Panama City Circuito RPC Television in Spanish 
2300 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1403164594 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Circuito RPC Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "RPC Television News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Justice and Peace Commission has publicly 
admonished the Democratic Revolutionary Party [PRD] for 
committing proven acts of violence against members of the 
Christian Democratic Party [PDC] on 6 March in La Chorrera 
District. A Justice and Peace Commission statement pointed out 
that although it is encouraging that PRD leaders, as well as 
members who perpetrated the acts, made apologies and rejected 
violence, the Commission wishes to remind everyone that the 
ethical agreement that was signed seeks to avoid and prevent 
incidents of this type and reiterates to the signatories their 
responsibility to honor this agreement. The Justice and Peace 
Commission urged all political parties and all citizens to stop 
insults and attacks and to seek together the path leading to a 
consensus. 
  Meanwhile, the PRD issued a communique accepting and 
respecting the Justice and Peace Commission's admonishment. It 
also called on the PRD Court of Honor and Discipline to apply 
the corresponding disciplinary measures to those members 
responsible for the attack. The PRD again prompted all its 
members to honor the commitments that the party made in the 
Santa Maria La Antigua Ethical-Electoral Pact. 

</TEXT>

