<H3> <TI>   Accord With Switzerland Prevents Double Taxation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1103183394 Quito Voz de los Andes in Spanish 2300 GMT 10 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1103183394 </F>
<F P=104>  Quito Voz de los Andes </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The Voz Andes Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] The international economic community is watching 
Ecuador closely and has confidence in the country and the 
macroeconomic policies instituted by the national government, a 
Foreign Ministry press bulletin has announced. The bulletin was 
issued on the occasion of the conclusion of negotiations for an 
agreement between Ecuador and Switzerland to prevent double 
taxation. 
  Approximately 70 companies and capital enterprises from the 
Swiss Confederation have invested or are investing $30 million 
in our country. This represents 7 percent of the total of 
direct foreign investments in Ecuador. This amount is surpassed 
only by Swiss investments in Argentina. 

</TEXT>

