<F P=102>  PY1103230894 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2135 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY1103230894 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Buenos Aires, 10 Mar (EFE) -- Gustavo Villalobos 
Sepulveda, executive secretary of the Chilean National Congress 
for Drug Control [Congreso Nacional para el Control de 
Estupefacientes de Chile], was today elected new president of 
the Inter-American Committee for the Control of Drugs and Drug 
Abuse (Cicad). 
  Villalobos, who will replace the Costa Rican Monica Berger, 
will be aided by Panamanian Attorney General Jorge Ramon Valdez. 
  The new Cicad president was elected to this post during the 
15th Cicad Congress that began on 8 March in Mar del Plata, 800 
km south of Buenos Aires. The congress will end 11 March. 
[passage omitted] 

