<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anti-Aristide Front Prepares To Fill `Power Vacuum' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1403220994 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1700 
GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1403220994 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A political forum took place at the Visa Lodge on 11 
March with the participation of political parties and 
organizations opposed to the return to Haiti of President 
Aristide. These organizations revealed their intention to form a 
political front to fill the current power vacuum. Discussions 
were held on the formation of an ad hoc government or a 
government of public safety. Following this meeting on 11 March, 
a nine-member committee in charge of preparing a resolution was 
established. 

</TEXT>

