<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujimori Supports Colombia's Gaviria for OAS Secretary 
General </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1403173794 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1512 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY1403173794 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Quito, 14 Mar (EFE) -- Peruvian President Alberto 
Fujimori supports the candidacy of his Colombian counterpart 
Cesar Gaviria for OAS secretary general because he always bets 
"on a winner." 
  In an interview published today in the Ecuadoran newspaper 
EL 
TELEGRAFO, Fujimori said: "We are promoting this candidacy. I 
bet on a winner and I hope Cesar Gaviria will win." 
  The Peruvian president added: "I have always been very clear 
on this issue. We have expressed our clear position of total 
support for President Gaviria." 
  Fujimori announced that his government is negotiating Peru's 
reintegration into the Andean Pact, which it abandoned in 1992. 
The Andean Pact comprises Colombia, Venezuela, Bolivia, and 
Ecuador. 
  Fujimori added: "This is a period of transition, of 
readjustment. I am sure the Andean Pact will continue and be 
strengthened with the reintegration of Peru." 
  The Peruvian president noted that he is not campaigning for 
reelection. 
  Fujimori said: "I do not want to talk about becoming a 
candidate. Of course, the (new) Constitution invites me, the 
people have invited me, but I have yet to decide." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

