<H3> <TI>   UN Secretary General Seeks Extension of Onusal Mandate </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1503220094 San Salvador Canal Doce Television in Spanish 
0300 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1503220094 </F>
<F P=104>  San Salvador Canal Doce Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Up-to-Date Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] Venezuelan Enrique Ter Horst was confirmed today by 
the UN Security Council as the UN representative and chief of 
the UN Observers for El Salvador [Onusal] mission which will 
have to take charge of the pending matters following the 
elections. UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali said that 
it will be necessary to extend Onusal's mission after 31 May 
when its mandate concludes. This is before the inauguration of 
the government elected during the 20 March elections as there is 
no prospect that by that date the peace agreements will be met. 
  UN Secretary General Butrus-Ghali made reference to the 
Salvadoran situation barely one week before the end of the 
electoral process indicating that although there have been some 
difficulties due to the delay in the delivery of voting 
documents in former conflict ridden areas, Onusal is negotiating 
with the authorities on the solution of this problem. 

</TEXT>

