<F P=102>  FL1503193094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1503193094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today, the foreign ministers of Cuba and Cambodia 
ratified the strong and friendly ties between the two nations 
and expressed that they are in favor of extending the ties of 
cooperation in all possible areas, especially the economy. 
  During his meeting with his Cambodian counterpart Norodom 
Sirivut, who is currently acting as the head of government, 
Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina reiterated the friendly 
ties that unite the two nations. Robaina also stated that his 
visit to Cambodia marks a new stage in bilateral relations and 
concurred with his counterpart in the hope of promoting an 
atmosphere of cooperation on economic and trade issues as well 
as updating the existing agreements between the two states. 
  Tomorrow, Cuban Foreign Minister Robaina will meet with Chea 
Sim, the acting head of state and president of Cambodia's 
National Assembly. Prior to his departure for India, the next 
stop of his tour, Robaina will hold a news conference. 

</TEXT>

