<H3> <TI>   Sugar Harvest Check Held in Granma Province </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1603005994 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2032 GMT 
15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1603005994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] With the slightest advantage over the eastern 
provinces, the nation's central provinces achieved the best 
performance in sugarcane harvest and recovery tasks in the first 
10 days of March. This was reported at the meeting held in 
Bayamo to check the progress of that economic sphere. Central 
Cuba's sugar agroindustrial complexes obtained superior results 
in yield, base 96 [not further identified], and in reducing 
electrical energy consumption, while they tied with those of the 
east in recovery and amount of sugar produced. 
  The agroindustrial complexes of western Cuba headed sugar 
recovery, making the best use of installed capabilities and cane 
planting. 
  The progress check for the first 10 days of the harvest in 
March, which was held in Bayamo, Granma Province, was presided 
over by Nelson Torres, minister of the Sugar Industry, and Jose 
Naranjo, chief of the team for coordination and support of the 
commander in chief. 

</TEXT>

