<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nation To Go on `Summer Time' on 2 Apr </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1603010694 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2039 GMT 
15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1603010694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Electric Union of the Ministry of Basic Industry 
has announced that summer time will go into effect throughout 
Cuba on 2 April at midnight, at which time clocks will be set 
forward one hour. The main objective of this traditional measure 
is to take maximum advantage of the light of the sun. Official 
time will be reestablished on 9 October, at 0100, at which time 
clocks will be set back 60 minutes. 

</TEXT>

