<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Germany Temporarily Suspends Diplomatic Presence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1603023794 Madrid EFE in Spanish 0046 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1603023794 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Port-au-Prince, 15 Mar (EFE) -- The German Embassy 
in Port-au-Prince today announced it will temporarily suspend 
its diplomatic presence in Haiti beginning 31 March because of 
Haiti's ongoing political crisis. This decision was made, 
according to an official communique, because the situation "does 
not allow the normal functioning of bilateral cooperation 
between the two countries." The communique adds that Germany's 
interests in Haiti will be represented after 31 March by the 
German Consulate in Miami and that German humanitarian aid will 
continue to flow through nongovernment organizations and 
churches. 
  Germany has traditional ties with Haiti and is one of the 
principal countries to offer aid to this Caribbean country. 
This aid includes the installation of hydroelectric plants over 
the past few years, as well as agricultural infrastructure 
assistance and scholarships for professionals and students. The 
Haitian-German Institute has been operating for one year in 
Port-au-Prince and offers classes in German. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

