<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Perez Balladares Favored </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1503222194 Panama City EL PANAMA AMERICA in Spanish 15 Mar 
94 p 1A </F>

<F P=103> PA1503222194 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City EL PANAMA AMERICA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Juan Pritsiolas] </F>
  [Text] Some 45 percent of Panamanians believe that 
[Democratic Revolutionary Party, PRD, presidential candidate] 
Ernesto Perez Balladares would favor creating a new military 
force, but also believe him to be the most reliable presidential 
candidate. These results were obtained in a nationwide poll 
conducted by the CID/GALLUP firm for EL PANAMA AMERICA during 
the week of 26 February-3 March. 
  Some 23 percent of 1,218 citizens polled did not answer the 
question on the creation of a military force. Some 19 percent 
of those polled said none of the seven candidates intend to 
create a military force. For 6 percent of those polled, Ruben 
Dario Carles intends to create a military force; while Mireya 
Moscoso de Gruber and Ruben Blades got 3 percent. The other 
presidential candidates registered 1 percent. 
  Regarding the most preferred candidate, three out of every 
10 
Panamanians said they prefer Perez Balladares. Carles obtained 
22 percent, Mireya Moscoso 11 percent, Blades 10 percent, while 
Eduardo Vallarino, Samuel Lewis Galindo, and Jose Salvador Munoz 
garnered 4 percent each. 

</TEXT>

