<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   ONIN Petition Supports Deputies' Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1503223594 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1700 
GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1503223594 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The National Organization for the Defense of 
National Interests [ONIN], which came out publicly on 14 March, 
denounces the irresponsibility of Haitian leaders toward the 
crisis. The movement, which favors the lower chamber's plan, 
called on all the sectors of national life to reach a compromise 
for a solution to the crisis. 
  ONIN, which openly opposes foreign domination of the 
country's internal affairs, on 14 March launched a petition 
throughout the country seeking signatures to support the plan 
proposed by the deputies, a petition that the members of the 
organization intend to submit to Army Headquarters on 29 March, 
the anniversary date of the 1987 Constitution. The members of 
the National Organization for the Defense of National Interests 
met with the press on 14 March. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

