<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bosque Urges Return to Target-Shooting Practice </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1603160494 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 0100 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1603160494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Gloria Guerrero from Granma] </F>
  [Text] Revolution Commander and Politburo member Juan 
Almeida Bosque, who is also chairman of the National Association 
of Veterans of the Revolution, has met with members of the 
secretariat of the Association of Cuban Revolution Veterans in 
Granma. Speaking in Bayamo, Almeida Bosque stressed the need to 
restore popular target-shooting practice and to encourage all 
the people to participate in this activity. 
  In a meeting with members of the Veterans secretariat, 
Almeida Bosque stressed the need to organize a movement for 
counseling children and young people to make target shooting a 
common practice if we want each Cuban to learn how to shoot and 
shoot well. 
  To achieve this, he recommended development through 
initiatives, contests, and other activities, but always with the 
objective of contributing to preparing the people for defense. 
  Accompanied by Division General Ramon Espinosa Martin, chief 
of the Eastern Army; Vice Admiral Aldo Santamaria Cuadrado; 
other chiefs and officers; and local Granma political leaders, 
Almeida Bosque expressed interest in current activities, in 
discipline, in patriotic-military work, and stressed as 
unavoidable the need for the association to be self-financed. 

</TEXT>

