<F P=100> SOUTH AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Butrus-Ghali Asks Menem To Sign NPT </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1603160394 Buenos Aires LA PRENSA in Spanish 15 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PY1603160394 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires LA PRENSA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali 
yesterday requested of President Carlos Menem that Argentina and 
Brazil expedite their support for the Nuclear Nonproliferation 
Treaty [NPT], and also praised the Argentine Government's 
efforts and constant willingness to send peacemaking forces to 
conflict regions. 
  Butrus-Ghali said that Argentina has become a leading 
country 
in Latin America and, despite his request, noted the efforts it 
has been making to ratify the nuclear weapon nonproliferation 
treaty. Menem, in turn, promised to hold talks with Brazil to 
this end. 
  This information was disclosed by Media Communications 
Secretary Raul Burzaco at the conclusion of the meeting held 
between Menem and Butrus-Ghali at Government House. 
  According to Burzaco, Menem and Butrus-Ghali never discussed 
the possibility of sending 200 Argentine servicemen stationed in 
Croatia to Bosnia. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

