<H3> <TI>   President Signs Freedom of Speech Declaration </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1503220994 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2113 GMT 12 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1503220994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 12 Mar (NOTIMEX) -- Mexican President 
Carlos Salinas de Gortari signed the Hemispheric Declaration on 
Freedom of Speech today at the end of a meeting with Latin 
American, U.S., and Canadian journalists. 
  After receiving a group of representatives to the 
Hemispheric 
Conference on Freedom of Speech, Carlos Salinas de Gortari 
reiterated his strict support for freedom of the press and 
emphasized the importance that the media have in modern society. 
During the meeting held at the presidential residence, the 
Mexican president said a free media helps the government to 
respond better to citizens' demands. He noted that criticism and 
freedom of speech in the media contribute to better decisions in 
favor of society with the rapidness and timeliness demanded by 
the people. 
  Those who attended the event included, among others, Jose 
Carreno Carlon, media director of the Presidency; Alejandro 
Junco de la Vega, REFORMA newspaper; and Claude Erbsen, 
Associated Press of New York. 

</TEXT>

