<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Czech Vice President Notes Further Consolidation of Ties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1703022294 Lima Global de Television Network in Spanish 
0100 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1703022294 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Global de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Diplomatic relations between the Czech Republic and 
Peru were further consolidated with the recent signature of two 
bilateral agreements. This was stated by Czech Republic Vice 
President Jan Kalvoda, who has been in Peru since 15 March on an 
official visit. 
  One of the agreements signed will promote and guarantee 
investments, which will benefit financial exchange, especially 
for national development products. The other agreement 
eliminates the requirement for visas for diplomatic passports. 
  During a news conference, the Czech vice president pointed 
out the trade exchange with Peru, which he described as 
important and balanced. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

